<h1 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h1>

<p>If you like the command line and enjoy listening to music online, you will probably fall in love with Tizoniaâ€™s simplicity and cleanliness. With the ability to stream music and play local content, this open source software is one of my favorites, although the gapless feature currently does not work with Spotify.</p>

<p>One of the many advantages of command line software is that they are generally more economical with system resources. When playing audio stored locally, Tizonia consumes only 18 MB of RAM. Spotify streaming consumed 34 MB of RAM, while streaming with the official GUI client weighed 612 MB!
Tizonia links</p>

